    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at Rail Vikas Nigam Advisory Limited. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Supply Chain Manager to strengthen our Pune-based team.\n\nAbout Rail Vikas Nigam Advisory Limited:\nRail Vikas Nigam Advisory Limited is a leading organization in the Hybrid sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Coordinate with warehousing teams for inbound and outbound operations\n• Implement cost-saving initiatives in transportation and warehousing\n• Track shipments in real-time and resolve delivery exceptions\n• Conduct periodic vendor audits and evaluate logistics partners\n• Handle customs clearance for import and export shipments\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Oversee end-to-end logistics operations for timely delivery\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• B.Tech / B.E. in Computer Science or related discipline\n• 6-10 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in Customs Clearance\n• Proficiency in Reverse Logistics\n• Proficiency in KPI Monitoring\n• Proficiency in 3PL Management\n• Proficiency in GPS Tracking Systems\n• Proficiency in SAP SCM\n• Proficiency in Data Analytics\n• Proficiency in TMS\n\nWork Mode: Hybrid - Flexible work-from-home and office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• Competitive salary with performance-linked incentives\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Mobile and internet reimbursement\n• Comprehensive health insurance for self and family\n• Learning & development budget\n• Employee stock options (ESOPs) for eligible roles\n• Salary Range: 12 LPA - 25 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Pune, Maharashtra, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with Rail Vikas Nigam Advisory Limited!",
